Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere Juan Gonzalez and Department of State Acting Assistant Secretary for Western Hemisphere Affairs Julie Chung will be traveling to Colombia, Argentina, and Uruguay from April 11 to 15. The purpose of their visit is to engage with government officials in these countries. In Bogota, they will focus on discussing economic recovery, security and rural development, the Venezuelan migrant crisis, and Colombia's regional climate leadership. In Argentina and Uruguay, they will discuss regional priorities, including addressing the challenges of the climate crisis and the COVID-19 pandemic, as well as threats to democracy, human rights, and security in the hemisphere and globally.